  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  written informed consent from parent/legal guardian and/or assent from child where
             appropriate as required by national legislation

          -  children aged 5-17 years (in Russia only: 12-17 years) with clinically stable chronic
             renal anemia;

          -  hemodialysis for &gt;=8 weeks;

          -  intravenous stable maintenance epoetin alfa, epoetin beta or darbepoetin alfa for &gt;=
             8 weeks before screening and with no weekly dose change &gt;/=25% (increase or decrease)
             during the 2 weeks of screening.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  overt gastrointestinal bleeding, or bleeding episode necessitating transfusion within
             8 weeks before screening;

          -  red blood cell (RBC) transfusions within 8 weeks before screening;

          -  active malignant disease;

          -  pure red cell aplasia (PRCA) or history of PRCA;

          -  pregnant or lactating;

          -  for sexually active patients: not willing to use reliable contraception.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
